---
// The frontmatter runs at build time. We just define the page title here.
const pageTitle = "allen su";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>{pageTitle}</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<p>allen su</p>
			<p>
				currently working on detecting quiet eval-awareness
				<a href="/quiet-eval-aware-writeup.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">preliminary writeup</a>,
				<a href="https://github.com/allensu02/quiet-eval-awareness" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">code</a>
			</p>
			<p class="previously">previously</p>
			<ul class="blurb">
				<li>
					founded and built
					<a href="https://codedreams.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Codedreams</a>,
					an AI tutor for iOS devs
				</li>
				<li>
					investigated neural data during complex movements with
					<a href="https://allenysu.wixsite.com/design-portfolio-all/osu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">cursor control tasks</a>
					and intracortical BCIs at
					<a href="https://www.braingate.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BrainGate</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					worked on poker &amp; tech at
					<a href="https://www.rf.team/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">RF Labs</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					built ML testing tooling on Apple's Proactive Intelligence team that
					powers Shortcuts and personal intelligence features like app suggestions
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>georgia tech</p>
			<p>human capital</p>
			<p class="links">
				<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/allensu02/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">linkedin</a>
				<a href="https://x.com/allenysu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">x</a>
				<a href="https://github.com/allensu02" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github</a>
				<span>allensu [at] gatech.edu</span>
			</p>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	/*
	 * Full black background.
	 * Setting it on html guarantees the color fills the whole viewport,
	 * even past the body's content box.
	 */
	html {
		background-color: #000000;
		color: #ffffff;
		font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	body {
		margin: 0;
		min-height: 100vh;
		padding: 2rem;
	}

	main p {
		margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
	}

	/*
	 * All inline links in the content are teal (same as the footer links).
	 * They only underline on hover to keep the page clean.
	 */
	main a {
		color: #5EEAD4;
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	main a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	/*
	 * "previously" label sits just above the bullet list, with a little
	 * space above to separate it from the current-work line.
	 */
	.previously {
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
	}

	/*
	 * The "previously" bullets. We cap the width for readability and use a
	 * small gap between items so each accomplishment reads as its own line.
	 */
	.blurb {
		max-width: 42rem;
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.blurb li {
		margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
	}

	/*
	 * The links line sits a bit below the three text lines.
	 * Using flex with a gap spaces the items evenly and wraps
	 * them cleanly on narrow screens.
	 */
	.links {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.links a {
		color: #5EEAD4;
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.links a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	.links span {
		color: #ffffff;
	}
</style>
